    "## 1. Introduction to MACD\n",
    "\n",
    "### What is MACD?\n",
    "The Moving Average Convergence Divergence (MACD) is a trend-following momentum indicator that shows the relationship between two exponential moving averages (EMAs) of a security's price. Developed by Gerald Appel in the late 1970s, it's one of the most widely used technical indicators in trading.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Why Use MACD?\n",
    "- **Trend Identification**: MACD helps identify the direction and strength of trends\n",
    "- **Momentum**: Measures the speed and direction of price movements\n",
    "- **Signal Generation**: Crossovers provide clear buy/sell signals\n",
    "- **Divergence**: Detects potential trend reversals\n",
    "\n",
    "### Best Timeframes and Markets\n",
    "- **Short-term**: MACD(12, 26, 9) for day trading\n",
    "- **Medium-term**: MACD(19, 39, 9) for swing trading\n",
    "- **Long-term**: MACD(50, 100, 16) for position trading\n",
    "- **Markets**: Works well in trending markets, less effective in ranging markets"
   ]
  },
